Insider and Institutional Ownership
70.7% of Elizabeth Arden shares are owned by institutional investors. Comparatively, 66.3% of Coty shares are owned by institutional investors. 15.2% of Elizabeth Arden shares are owned by insiders. Comparatively, 16.1% of Coty shares are owned by insiders. Strong institutional ownership is an indication that hedge funds, endowments and large money managers believe a stock will outperform the market over the long term.
Risk and Volatility
Elizabeth Arden has a beta of 1.35, suggesting that its stock price is 35% more volatile than the S&P 500. Comparatively, Coty has a beta of 0.28, suggesting that its stock price is 72% less volatile than the S&P 500. 
