                                                    Coty posts bigger loss due to charges related to P&G deal
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    6:47 AM ET 05/10/2017
                                                


Beauty products maker Coty Inc (COTY) reported a bigger quarterly loss, hurt by restructuring charges related to the integration of the beauty business it acquired from Procter & Gamble Co. Net loss attributable to Coty (COTY) increased to $164.2 million, or 22 cents per share, in the third quarter ended March 31, from $26.8 million, or 8 cents per share, a year earlier.

















